Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Lay the @British Chicken Breasts{2} onto a large #baking tray{}, drizzle with oil, sprinkle over half the @Indonesian Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast the chicken on the top shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large, wide-bottomed #ovenproof pan{} with a #lid{} on medium heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an ovenproof dish before baking.

Add the @Yellow Thai Style Paste{45%g}, @Ginger Puree{15%g} and remaining Indonesian style spice mix. Fry for ~{30%secs}.

Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g} and @Water{300%ml}.

Bring to the boil, then pop the lid on the pan (or cover with #foil{}) and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, crush the @Salted Peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

Once the rice is cooked, remove it from the oven and stir in the @Peas{120%g}, @Soy Sauce{15%ml}, @Honey{2%tbsp} and @Butter{20%g}.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed, then pop the lid back on and allow to sit until the peas are piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once the chicken is cooked, transfer it to a clean board and allow it to rest for a couple of mins.

Once rested, thinly slice widthways.

Serve the baked rice with the sliced chicken on top.

Drizzle over the @Sweet Chilli Sauce{32%g} and @Mayonnaise{2%tbsp}.

Scatter over the peanuts to finish.

Enjoy!